            "answer_text": "The only secret that was lost when Rome collapsed in 476 AD was how to make pozzolana concrete. Even the Eastern Romans had to build the Hagia Sophia with brick, stone & lime mortar only. Once they lost the Italian peninsula to the Goths & Lombards in the 500s AD. They lost access to the only source of pozzolan volcanic ash near Naples. Ancient Roman Concrete Was Inspired By Volcanic Chemistry Seawater is the secret to long-lasting Roman concrete ",
